# Copy to `.dev.vars` (gitignored) and fill in. Two distinct credential types below.

# ── Worker runtime secrets ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are the agent's own secrets. Used by `wrangler dev`; for production they
# are pushed with `wrangler secret put <NAME>` (the tooling reads the values here).
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="sk-ant-..."
QBO_CLIENT_ID=""            # Intuit Developer app → Keys & Credentials
QBO_CLIENT_SECRET=""        # Intuit Developer app → Keys & Credentials
# Only when a tenant uses inference_provider = 'bedrock' (AU residency path):
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=""
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=""

# ── wrangler CLI auth (control plane — NOT a Worker secret) ───────────────
# This is wrangler's login to your Cloudflare account, used to create D1/R2/KV and
# deploy. It is read from the environment by the tooling, not by the Worker.
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=""     # token with: Workers Scripts Edit, D1 Edit, KV Edit, R2 Edit
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=""  # only if `wrangler whoami` shows more than one account
